    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-26T11:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-26T11:30:00-05:00" n="930"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d930">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7331A15/25: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Venezuela</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caracas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-26T12:00:00-04:30"
                            >October 26, 1929—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 10:35 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>172. Legation’s 162, October 3, 8 p.m.<note n="5" xml:id="d930fn5">Not
                        printed.</note> All America Cables has now received permit in writing to
                    operate French cable to Venezuela and to lay new cable from La Guayra to Curaçao
                    and thence to Maracaibo. Duration of nineteen to twenty years and the tax
                    payable to the Venezuelan Government has been fixed at twelve and a half percent
                    on the gross receipts exclusive of government messages. Company agrees not to
                    charge less than government radio rate.</p>
                <p>This brings to a successful conclusion negotiations since 1922 and gives
                    Venezuela a modern cable service which for the first time links it up with All
                    America System.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
